## What
Restructure Mph::lookup_key_index to use MphBackend trait methods instead of directly accessing ChdBackend::slot_to_key_idx. Currently, the method reaches into backend-specific internal state, meaning a backend swap would require modifying Mph::lookup_key_index — violating the trait abstraction contract.

## Why
The MphBackend trait exists as an abstraction boundary (bd-wa5p postcondition 3). Direct field access couples the Mph wrapper to ChdBackend's internal representation. When PtrHash replaces CHD (ADR-FERR-030 Phase 4c+ plan), a PtrHashBackend would not have slot_to_key_idx and lookup_key_index would fail to compile.

## Acceptance
1. MphBackend trait gains reverse_lookup(&self, slot: usize) -> Option<usize> method.
2. ChdBackend::reverse_lookup delegates to slot_to_key_idx.
3. Mph::lookup_key_index uses self.backend.reverse_lookup(slot) instead of self.backend.slot_to_key_idx.get(slot).
4. Mph::lookup_key_index does NOT access any ChdBackend fields directly.
5. All existing mph tests pass unchanged.
6. Zero clippy warnings. cargo test --workspace passes.

