## Pseudocode Contract

```rust
// --- MphBackend trait addition ---

pub(crate) trait MphBackend: Clone + std::fmt::Debug {
    fn build(sorted_keys: &[EntityId]) -> Option<Self> where Self: Sized;
    fn lookup(&self, key: &EntityId) -> usize;

    /// Reverse lookup: slot -> key index in the original sorted key array.
    /// Returns None if the slot is unoccupied (non-minimal hash overflow slot).
    fn reverse_lookup(&self, slot: usize) -> Option<usize>;
}

// --- ChdBackend implementation ---

impl MphBackend for ChdBackend {
    // ... existing build/lookup ...

    fn reverse_lookup(&self, slot: usize) -> Option<usize> {
        let raw = self.slot_to_key_idx.get(slot).copied().unwrap_or(u32::MAX);
        if raw == u32::MAX {
            None
        } else {
            Some(raw as usize)
        }
    }
}

// --- Mph::lookup_key_index (modified) ---

impl Mph {
    pub(crate) fn lookup_key_index(&self, key: &EntityId) -> Option<usize> {
        if self.keys.is_empty() {
            return None;
        }
        let slot = self.backend.lookup(key);
        let key_idx = self.backend.reverse_lookup(slot)?;
        if key_idx < self.keys.len() && self.keys[key_idx] == *key {
            Some(key_idx)
        } else {
            None
        }
    }
}
```

## Refinement Sketch
- **Abstract**: The MphBackend trait defines the backend-agnostic contract. lookup maps key -> slot. reverse_lookup maps slot -> key_index. Together they provide the building blocks for Mph::contains and lookup_key_index without backend-specific coupling.
- **Concrete**: ChdBackend::reverse_lookup reads slot_to_key_idx. PtrHashBackend::reverse_lookup would use its Elias-Fano remap table. The Mph wrapper sees only the trait.
- **Coupling**: bd-wa5p postcondition 3 verified by: grep for ChdBackend field access outside ChdBackend impl block -> zero matches.

## Edge Cases
| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| slot >= slot_to_key_idx.len() | Vec::get returns None -> reverse_lookup returns None |
| slot_to_key_idx[slot] == u32::MAX | Unoccupied overflow slot -> reverse_lookup returns None |
| Valid slot | Returns Some(key_index) for key comparison |

