## What
Replace `Attribute(Arc<str>)` with `AttributeId(u16)` throughout the hot paths. A bidirectional intern table (`AttributeIntern`) maps between string names and u16 IDs. Attribute comparison becomes integer comparison (1 cycle). Clone becomes Copy (0 cycles). Per-datom memory drops ~38 bytes.

## Why
Attribute is the highest-compression-opportunity field in the datom model. NEG-FERR-007 shows: ~50 unique attributes in a typical store, H₀ ≈ 2.5 bits/byte, currently stored as ~30 bytes (Arc pointer + refcount + string). Interning to u16 gives:
- Comparison: 1 cycle (was: pointer deref + string compare, ~20ns)
- Clone: 0 cycles (Copy, was: Arc refcount bump, ~5ns)
- Memory: 2 bytes (was: ~30 bytes including Arc overhead)
- At 100K datoms: 2.8MB saved on attribute field alone

This is the prerequisite for SoA columnar (bd-574c) and wavelet matrix (ADR-FERR-030). The intern table IS the column dictionary.

## Preconditions
1. Attribute is `Arc<str>` in ferratom/src/datom/value.rs.
2. Schema already maintains a mapping of known attributes.
3. Genesis schema has 19 bootstrap attributes.

## Postconditions
