```rust
// --- Mph struct modification ---

/// CHD Perfect Hash with entity-to-position mapping (INV-FERR-027).
#[derive(Clone, Debug)]
pub(crate) struct Mph {
    backend: ChdBackend,
    keys: Vec<EntityId>,
    /// entity_first_pos[i] = canonical position of first datom for keys[i].
    /// Built during construction in the same O(n) pass as unique_entity_ids.
    entity_first_pos: Vec<u32>,
}

impl Mph {
    /// Build from sorted unique EntityIds and their first canonical positions.
    pub(crate) fn build(
        sorted_keys: Vec<EntityId>,
        first_positions: Vec<u32>,
    ) -> Option<Self> {
        debug_assert_eq!(sorted_keys.len(), first_positions.len());
        let backend = ChdBackend::build(&sorted_keys)?;
        Some(Self {
            backend,
            keys: sorted_keys,
            entity_first_pos: first_positions,
        })
    }

    /// O(1) entity -> first canonical position.
    /// Returns None if entity is absent from the construction set.
    pub(crate) fn entity_position(&self, key: &EntityId) -> Option<u32> {
        let key_idx = self.lookup_key_index(key)?;
        self.entity_first_pos.get(key_idx).copied()
    }
}

// --- PositionalStore modifications ---

impl PositionalStore {
    /// Sorted unique EntityIds AND their first canonical positions.
    /// O(n) single pass over canonical array.
    fn unique_entities_with_positions(&self) -> (Vec<EntityId>, Vec<u32>) {
        let mut keys = Vec::new();
        let mut positions = Vec::new();
        let mut prev: Option<EntityId> = None;
        for (i, datom) in self.canonical.iter().enumerate() {
            let eid = datom.entity();
            if prev.as_ref() != Some(&eid) {
                keys.push(eid);
                positions.push(u32::try_from(i).unwrap_or(u32::MAX));
                prev = Some(eid);
            }
        }
        (keys, positions)
    }

    /// O(1) entity existence check + position lookup (INV-FERR-027).
    /// Both positive and negative paths are O(1).
    #[must_use]
    pub fn entity_lookup(&self, eid: &EntityId) -> Option<u32> {
        let mph_opt = self.mph.get_or_init(|| {
            let (keys, positions) = self.unique_entities_with_positions();
            Mph::build(keys, positions)
        });

        if let Some(mph) = mph_opt {
            return mph.entity_position(eid);
        }

        // MPH build failed -> binary search fallback
        self.first_datom_position_for_entity(eid)
    }
}
```

## Refinement Sketch
- **Abstract**: rank(EntityId) in O(1) via MPH. position(rank) in O(1) via precomputed array. Composition: position(rank(EntityId)) in O(1).
- **Concrete**: During unique_entities_with_positions(), both the sorted key array and the first-position array are built in the same O(n) scan. Mph::build takes both. entity_position composes lookup_key_index (O(1) via MPH) with array index (O(1)).
- **Coupling**: INV-FERR-027 latency target. entity_first_pos is the bridge between the rank domain (MPH) and the position domain (PositionalStore).

## Edge Cases
| Scenario | Behavior |
|----------|----------|
| Empty store | Mph not built (empty keys). entity_lookup returns None. |
| Absent entity | MPH lookup_key_index returns None -> entity_position returns None. O(1). |
| Present entity | MPH lookup_key_index returns rank -> entity_first_pos[rank] -> O(1). |
| MPH build fails | Fallback to partition_point (O(log n)). |

