## Performance Context
After promote, reads regress 30ns→300ns, LIVE 1ns→200ns. Demotion restores Positional after transact. With lazy perms (bd-vhmc), demotion is O(n): collect OrdSet→Vec (already sorted) + build_live_bitvector. At 200K: ~2ms. Batch at group commit boundary: ~20μs amortized at batch size 100.

## Resolved Type Decisions
1. demote() builds PositionalStore from OrdMap's OrdSet iter (EAVT-sorted → sort_unstable detects O(n))
2. Wrap in Arc for StoreRepr::Positional(Arc::new(pos))
3. live_causal/live_set STAY on Store — not rebuilt by demote (already correct from transact-time live_apply calls)
4. batch_replay promotes once, replays all entries, demotes once — replaces N×replay_entry in Database::open
5. transact() calls demote() AFTER building TxReceipt, BEFORE returning Ok

## Pseudocode — Store::demote() (NEW in store/mod.rs, alongside promote())

```rust
impl Store {
    /// Demote from OrdMap back to Positional (INV-FERR-072).
    ///
    /// Rebuilds PositionalStore from OrdMap's OrdSet. O(n) because:
    /// - OrdSet iteration is EAVT-sorted → sort_unstable detects sorted run O(n)
    /// - build_live_bitvector is O(n)
    /// - Permutation arrays are OnceLock::new() (lazy, bd-vhmc)
    /// No-op if already Positional.
    pub(crate) fn demote(&mut self) {
        if let StoreRepr::OrdMap { datoms, .. } = &self.repr {
            // OrdSet iterates in Datom Ord (= EAVT) order.
            // PositionalStore::from_datoms receives already-sorted input.
            let positional = PositionalStore::from_datoms(datoms.iter().cloned());
            self.repr = StoreRepr::Positional(Arc::new(positional));
        }
    }
}
```

