## What
Eliminate the Vec<EntityId> keys array from Mph. Verify-after-lookup should read from PositionalStore::canonical instead of a duplicate key array. At 200K unique entities, the keys array is 6.4 MB (32 bytes × 200K). These EntityIds already exist in the canonical datom array.

## Why
Memory efficiency: 32 bytes/key is the dominant cost of the MPH structure. The ChdBackend itself is ~5 bytes/key. Eliminating keys reduces total MPH overhead from ~37 bytes/key to ~9 bytes/key (backend + entity_first_pos). At 100M unique entities: saves ~3.2 GB.

## Acceptance
1. Mph struct does NOT contain Vec<EntityId>.
2. Verify-after-lookup reads entity from canonical[entity_first_pos[key_idx]].entity().
3. PositionalStore::entity_lookup passes &self.canonical to the verification step.
4. Memory per MPH: ChdBackend (~5 bytes/key) + entity_first_pos (4 bytes/key) = ~9 bytes/key.
5. All existing mph tests pass (adapted to new API).
6. Zero clippy warnings. cargo test --workspace passes.

